quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,75,"Even if We were to show them mercy and relieve their adversity<sup>34</sup>, they would still persist in their transgression, wandering blindly.","[34] It refers to the famine which occurred in Makkah some time after the advent of prophethood."
  23,76,"We have already seized them with punishment, but they did not humble themselves to their Lord, nor did they supplicate in humility,",""
  23,77,"until when We open for them a gateway of severe punishment, they will be plunged into utter despair.",""
  23,78,"It is He Who gave you hearing, sight and hearts. How little you give thanks<sup>35</sup>!","[35] The disbelievers, instead of showing gratefulness for the blessings of eyes, ears, mind, and heart; show ingratitude to their Creator."
  23,79,"And it is He Who spread you on earth, and to Him you will all be gathered.",""
  23,80,"It is He Who gives life and causes death, and to Him belongs the alternation of night and day<sup>36</sup>. Do you not understand?","[36] The One Who possesses all these powers is the only One worthy of worship without any partners with Him."
  23,81,"But<sup>37</sup> they say the like of what the earlier peoples said.","[37] Instead of using their understanding and reason."
  23,82,"They say, “Is it that when we die and become dust and bones, will we really be resurrected<sup>38</sup>?","[38] The One Who created the earth and everything on it from nothing, it is easy for Him to re-create them once again."
  23,83,"This is what we and our forefathers were promised before; this is nothing but ancient fables.”",""
  23,84,"Say, “To whom belong the earth and all those who are on it, if you really know?”",""
  23,85,"They will say, “To Allah.” Say, “Will you not then take heed?”",""
  23,86,"Say, “Who is the Lord of the seven heavens and the Lord of the Mighty Throne?”",""
  23,87,"They will say, “Allah.” Say, “Will you not then fear Him?”",""
  23,88,"Say, “In Whose Hand is the dominion of all things – and He gives protection while none can protect against Him – if you really know?”",""
  23,89,"They will say, “Allah.” Say, “Then how can you be deluded?”",""
